                        Ambassador in China (
                        Stuart
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1365</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1365</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-07-21T16:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-07-21T16:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-21T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="1365" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1365">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.76/6–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-21T17:00:00-04:00">July 21, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>865. ConGen Tientsin tel 321, May 16, rptd Nanking 202, Shanghai 224, Peiping
                    140, Hong Kong unnumbered; Embtel 1172 June 2 rptd Peiping 189, Hong Kong 30,
                    Tientsin 36.</p>
                <p>Dept not in position object unilateral action Brit firm in establishing
                    Tientsin–Hong Kong radio communications since Dept has indicated to RCA<note n="95" xml:id="d1365fn95">Radio Corporation of America.</note> no objection
                    its negotiating with Commie authorities for North China circuit via Manila. No
                    evidence at present Chi Commie discrimination against RCA.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
